Note: ===================================================================
Note: CMAKE SEMANTIC ANALYZER
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Semantic analysis for CMake build system definitions. Handles target
Note: validation, dependency analysis, variable resolution, generator
Note: expression validation, and CMake best practices enforcement.

Note: Part of the Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/cmake/cmake_semantic.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/cmake/cmake_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict

Note: ===================================================================
Note: SEMANTIC ANALYZER STRUCTURE
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
CMake's "language" is really a build-system declarative engine layered on a
macro-style command interpreter. Semantic analysis therefore tracks many
parallel namespaces: targets (executables/libraries), free variables,
function/macro definitions, include lists, subdirectories, cached
properties, policies (CMP00xx behavior selectors), generators, dependency
edges, target-link sets, compile definitions, and include directories. Each
gets its own Dict so lookups remain O(1) regardless of project size.
Separate validation_errors/validation_warnings streams keep severity ordering
intact for the diagnostic reporter, and circular_dependencies/undefined_*
caches collect graph-analysis output without re-walking the build graph.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
176-byte record (22 x i64 slots, offsets 0..168): every "registry" slot is
either a Dict (for keyed lookups like targets/variables) or a List (for
ordered streams like validation_errors). The cmake_minimum_version slot at
offset 168 is parsed from the first cmake_minimum_required() command and
gates policy enforcement. has_error is sticky; error_message holds the
first failure's owned StringCore.
@End Implementation

Type called "CMakeSemanticAnalyzer":
    targets as Integer
    variables as Integer
    functions as Integer
    macros as Integer
    includes as Integer
    subdirectories as Integer
    properties as Integer
    policies as Integer
    generators as Integer
    dependencies as Integer
    target_links as Integer
    compile_definitions as Integer
    include_directories as Integer
    circular_dependencies as Integer
    undefined_targets as Integer
    undefined_variables as Integer
    policy_warnings as Integer
    validation_errors as Integer
    validation_warnings as Integer
    error_message as Integer
    has_error as Integer
    cmake_minimum_version as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: ANALYZER CREATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates the 176-byte analyzer record with all registries pre-populated.
Empty dicts/lists rather than null pointers so later phases never need to
null-check before adding entries, simplifying the hot paths.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
22-field struct at 8-byte slots: targets/variables/functions/macros dicts,
includes/subdirectories lists, properties/policies/dependencies dicts,
target_links, definitions, include_directories, plus validation accumulators
(circular_dependencies, undefined_*, policy_warnings, validation_*).
@End Implementation
Process called "create_cmake_semantic_analyzer" returns Integer:
    Note: Create CMake semantic analyzer for build system validation

    Let analyzer_size be 176
    Let analyzer be proc allocate from Layout with analyzer_size

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let targets be proc create from Dict
    Let variables be proc create from Dict
    Let functions be proc create from Dict
    Let macros be proc create from Dict
    Let includes be proc create from List
    Let subdirectories be proc create from List
    Let properties be proc create from Dict
    Let policies be proc create from Dict
    Let generators be proc create from List
    Let dependencies be proc create from Dict
    Let target_links be proc create from Dict
    Let compile_definitions be proc create from Dict
    Let include_directories be proc create from Dict
    Let circular_dependencies be proc create from List
    Let undefined_targets be proc create from List
    Let undefined_variables be proc create from List
    Let policy_warnings be proc create from List
    Let validation_errors be proc create from List
    Let validation_warnings be proc create from List

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0, targets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8, variables
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16, functions
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24, macros
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 32, includes
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 40, subdirectories
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 48, properties
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 56, policies
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64, generators
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72, dependencies
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 80, target_links
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 88, compile_definitions
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 96, include_directories
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 104, circular_dependencies
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 112, undefined_targets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 120, undefined_variables
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128, policy_warnings
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 136, validation_errors
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 144, validation_warnings
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 152, 0  Note: error_message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 160, 0  Note: has_error
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 168, 0  Note: cmake_minimum_version

    Return analyzer
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN ANALYSIS ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Six-phase analysis: collect declarations, resolve dependencies, validate
targets, analyse variables/generators, check policies, detect cycles.
Ordering is mandatory because each phase depends on the previous one
having populated the registries.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_cmake_project" takes analyzer as Integer, cmake_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Perform complete semantic analysis on CMake project

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If cmake_ast is equal to 0:
        proc set_cmake_semantic_error with analyzer, "Null CMake AST"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Phase 1: Collect targets, variables, and declarations
    proc collect_cmake_declarations with analyzer, cmake_ast

    Note: Phase 2: Resolve dependencies and references
    proc resolve_cmake_dependencies from analyzer

    Note: Phase 3: Validate targets and properties
    proc validate_cmake_targets from analyzer

    Note: Phase 4: Analyze variables and generator expressions
    proc analyze_cmake_variables from analyzer

    Note: Phase 5: Check policies and version requirements
    proc validate_cmake_policies from analyzer

    Note: Phase 6: Detect circular dependencies
    proc detect_cmake_circular_dependencies from analyzer

    Let has_error be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 160
    If has_error is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: DECLARATION COLLECTION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 1: walks every top-level CMake command and dispatches on command
name through a Match statement. Routes targets/variables/functions/macros
to their type-specific collectors so the registries are populated before
dependency resolution begins.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_declarations" takes analyzer as Integer, cmake_ast as Integer:
    Note: Collect all CMake declarations for reference resolution

    Let commands be proc get_cmake_commands from cmake_ast
    Let command_count be proc size from List with commands
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than command_count:
        Let command be proc get from List with commands, i
        Let command_name be proc get_cmake_command_name from command

        Match command_name:
            When "cmake_minimum_required":
                proc collect_cmake_minimum_version with analyzer, command
            When "project":
                proc collect_cmake_project with analyzer, command
            When "add_executable":
                proc collect_cmake_executable_target with analyzer, command
            When "add_library":
                proc collect_cmake_library_target with analyzer, command
            When "add_custom_target":
                proc collect_cmake_custom_target with analyzer, command
            When "set":
                proc collect_cmake_variable with analyzer, command
            When "function":
                proc collect_cmake_function with analyzer, command
            When "macro":
                proc collect_cmake_macro with analyzer, command
            When "include":
                proc collect_cmake_include with analyzer, command
            When "add_subdirectory":
                proc collect_cmake_subdirectory with analyzer, command
            When "set_property":
                proc collect_cmake_property with analyzer, command
            When "cmake_policy":
                proc collect_cmake_policy with analyzer, command
            When _:
                Note: Other commands analyzed in later phases
        End Match

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores the cmake_minimum_required version in the analyzer at offset 168
so later phases (validate_cmake_policies, check_minimum_version_requirements)
can validate version-gated features against this minimum.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_minimum_version" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect CMake minimum version requirement

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is greater than 1:
        Let version_arg be proc get from List with args, 1
        Let version_value be proc extract_cmake_version from version_arg
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 168, version_value
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
project() defines the build's project metadata. We store the project name
as a variable so subsequent ${PROJECT_NAME} references resolve correctly,
then process auxiliary args (VERSION, LANGUAGES, etc.).
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_project" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect project declaration

    @Reasoning:
    Project command defines project name, version, languages, and
    description. Validate project structure and track project-level
    settings for proper CMake project organization.
    @End Reasoning

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is greater than 0:
        Let project_name be proc get from List with args, 0
        Let variables be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
        proc set from Dict with variables, "PROJECT_NAME", project_name

        Note: Validate project name conventions
        proc validate_project_name with analyzer, project_name
    End If

    Note: Process additional project arguments (VERSION, LANGUAGES, etc.)
    proc process_project_arguments with analyzer, args
End Process

@Reasoning:
add_executable(name srcs...) registers an executable target. We reject
empty arg lists, duplicate target names, and missing sources. The target
record stores "executable" as type so later validators can apply
executable-specific rules (e.g., entry point required).
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_executable_target" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect executable target definition

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is equal to 0:
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, "add_executable command missing target name"
        Return
    End If

    Let target_name be proc get from List with args, 0
    Let targets_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0

    Note: Check for duplicate target
    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with targets_registry, target_name
    If exists is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Duplicate target: ", target_name
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    Let target_info be proc create_target_info with "executable", args
    proc set from Dict with targets_registry, target_name, target_info

    Note: Validate source files
    proc validate_target_sources with analyzer, target_name, args
End Process

@Reasoning:
add_library() has four flavours (STATIC, SHARED, MODULE, INTERFACE) which
determine linking behaviour. determine_library_type extracts the flavour
from the arg list (or falls back to the project default) so subsequent
linking validation knows which constraints apply.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_library_target" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect library target definition

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is equal to 0:
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, "add_library command missing target name"
        Return
    End If

    Let target_name be proc get from List with args, 0
    Let targets_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0

    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with targets_registry, target_name
    If exists is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Duplicate target: ", target_name
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    Note: Determine library type (STATIC, SHARED, MODULE, INTERFACE)
    Let library_type be proc determine_library_type from args
    Let target_info be proc create_target_info with library_type, args
    proc set from Dict with targets_registry, target_name, target_info

    Note: Validate library-specific constraints
    proc validate_library_target with analyzer, target_name, library_type, args
End Process

@Reasoning:
set(name value) registers a variable. Naming conventions are validated
(uppercase recommended) and reserved-name conflicts are flagged. CACHE
and PARENT_SCOPE qualifiers in extra args are not handled here; they're
processed in later phases.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_variable" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect variable assignment

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is less than 2:
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, "set command requires variable name and value"
        Return
    End If

    Let variable_name be proc get from List with args, 0
    Let variable_value be proc get from List with args, 1
    Let variables_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8

    Note: Check for special variable naming conventions
    proc validate_variable_name with analyzer, variable_name

    proc set from Dict with variables_registry, variable_name, variable_value
End Process

@Reasoning:
function() introduces a new variable scope, distinct from macro() which
expands inline. We warn on redefinition (CMake silently allows it but
behaviour can surprise) and store the command for later validation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_cmake_function" takes analyzer as Integer, command as Integer:
    Note: Collect function definition

    Let args be proc get_cmake_command_arguments from command
    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args

    If arg_count is equal to 0:
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, "function command missing function name"
        Return
    End If

    Let function_name be proc get from List with args, 0
    Let functions_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16

    Let exists be proc contains from Dict with functions_registry, function_name
    If exists is equal to 1:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Function redefinition: ", function_name
        proc add_cmake_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
    End If

    proc set from Dict with functions_registry, function_name, command
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: DEPENDENCY RESOLUTION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 2 orchestrator: resolves target-link relationships, generic target
dependencies, variable references, then assembles the dependency graph
used by detect_cmake_circular_dependencies in phase 6.
@End Reasoning
Process called "resolve_cmake_dependencies" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Resolve all target dependencies and references

    proc resolve_target_link_dependencies from analyzer
    proc resolve_target_dependencies from analyzer
    proc resolve_variable_references from analyzer
    proc build_cmake_dependency_graph from analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks every target_link_libraries() command and records link edges into
the target_links registry. Executables can link to libraries; libraries
can link to other libraries with visibility (PUBLIC/PRIVATE/INTERFACE)
controlling propagation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "resolve_target_link_dependencies" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Resolve target_link_libraries dependencies

    Note: This  analyze target_link_libraries commands in the AST
    Note: and build the link dependency relationships
    Let targets_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let target_links be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 80

    Note: For each target_link_libraries command found in AST
    Note:  register the linking relationship
    Note: Implementation  iterate through commands and collect links
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TARGET VALIDATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 3 orchestrator: validates target definitions, properties, source
files, and naming conventions. Property validation runs after definition
because some properties (e.g., LINK_FLAGS) only make sense for certain
target types.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_cmake_targets" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate target definitions and properties

    proc validate_target_definitions from analyzer
    proc validate_target_properties from analyzer
    proc validate_target_sources from analyzer
    proc check_target_naming_conventions from analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Per-target validation walker; iterates every registered target and runs
name validation plus per-type constraint checks. Type-specific validation
is delegated through validate_target_type_constraints.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_target_definitions" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate target definition correctness

    Let targets_registry be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let target_names be proc keys from Dict with targets_registry
    Let target_count be proc size from List with target_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than target_count:
        Let target_name be proc get from List with target_names, i
        Let target_info be proc get from Dict with targets_registry, target_name

        Note: Validate target name conventions
        proc validate_target_name with analyzer, target_name

        Note: Validate target type constraints
        Let target_type be proc get_target_type from target_info
        proc validate_target_type_constraints with analyzer, target_name, target_type

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
CMake target names must not contain spaces (parsing ambiguity), should
avoid reserved names (e.g., ALL, test), and conventionally use lowercase.
Each rule produces a distinct error/warning so build authors can fix
issues incrementally.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_target_name" takes analyzer as Integer, target_name as Integer:
    Note: Validate CMake target naming conventions

    Note: Check for invalid characters
    Let has_spaces be proc string_contains from StringCore with target_name, " "
    If has_spaces is equal to 1:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Target name contains spaces: ", target_name
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, error
    End If

    Note: Check for reserved names
    Let is_reserved be proc is_cmake_reserved_name from target_name
    If is_reserved is equal to 1:
        Let warning be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Target name conflicts with CMake reserved name: ", target_name
        proc add_cmake_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
    End If

    Note: Check naming conventions (lowercase recommended)
    proc check_target_naming_style with analyzer, target_name
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: VARIABLE ANALYSIS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 4 orchestrator: variable definition analysis -> undefined-use
detection -> generator-expression validation -> cache-variable checks.
Generator expressions are validated separately because they have their
own mini-grammar ($<COND:value>).
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_cmake_variables" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Analyze variable usage and generator expressions

    proc analyze_variable_definitions from analyzer
    proc check_undefined_variable_usage from analyzer
    proc validate_generator_expressions from analyzer
    proc check_cache_variable_usage from analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Iterates every generator expression collected during phase 1 and validates
each through validate_individual_generator_expression. Errors accumulate
into the analyser's error list rather than aborting the pass.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_generator_expressions" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate CMake generator expressions

    Let generators be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 64
    Let generator_count be proc size from List with generators
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than generator_count:
        Let generator_expr be proc get from List with generators, i
        proc validate_individual_generator_expression with analyzer, generator_expr
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates a single generator expression: must start with "$<" and end
with ">". The colon-separated form $<COND:value> is extracted by finding
the first ":"; the bare form $<COND> takes the entire content as the
generator name.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_individual_generator_expression" takes analyzer as Integer, generator_expr as Integer:
    Note: Validate individual generator expression

    Note: Check basic syntax (starts with $< and ends with >)
    Let starts_with_gen be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with generator_expr, "$<"
    Let ends_with_gen be proc string_ends_with from StringCore with generator_expr, ">"

    If starts_with_gen is equal to 0 or ends_with_gen is equal to 0:
        Let error be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Invalid generator expression syntax: ", generator_expr
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, error
        Return
    End If

    Note: Extract generator name and validate
    Let generator_content be proc string_substring from StringCore with generator_expr, 2, proc string_length from StringCore with generator_expr minus 3
    Let colon_pos be proc string_find from StringCore with generator_content, ":"

    If colon_pos is not equal to -1:
        Let generator_name be proc string_substring from StringCore with generator_content, 0, colon_pos
        proc validate_generator_name with analyzer, generator_name
    Otherwise:
        proc validate_generator_name with analyzer, generator_content
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: POLICY VALIDATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 5 orchestrator: checks minimum-version compliance, policy settings
correctness, and flags deprecated features. CMake policies (CMP00xx) gate
behavioural changes between CMake versions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_cmake_policies" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Validate CMake policies and version compatibility

    proc check_minimum_version_requirements from analyzer
    proc validate_policy_settings from analyzer
    proc check_deprecated_features from analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
cmake_minimum_required() is mandatory in well-formed CMake projects -
missing it generates an error. Once present, the version is validated
through validate_cmake_version_appropriateness to flag stale (<3.0) or
too-new (>4.x) baselines.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_minimum_version_requirements" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Check CMake minimum version requirements

    Let cmake_version be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 168

    If cmake_version is equal to 0:
        proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, "Missing cmake_minimum_required command"
        Return
    End If

    Note: Check version is reasonable (not too old or too new)
    proc validate_cmake_version_appropriateness with analyzer, cmake_version
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CIRCULAR DEPENDENCY DETECTION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Phase 6: DFS-based cycle detection over the target dependency graph. Runs
detect_cycle_from_cmake_target for every target with fresh visited/visiting
sets. Cycles are accumulated rather than aborting so multiple independent
cycles can be reported at once.
@End Reasoning
Process called "detect_cmake_circular_dependencies" takes analyzer as Integer:
    Note: Detect circular dependencies in target graph

    @Reasoning:
    Sixth phase uses depth-first search to detect circular dependencies
    in target link graph and add_dependencies graph. Circular dependencies
    cause build failures and must be detected early.
    @End Reasoning

    Let dependencies be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72
    Let visited be proc create from Dict
    Let visiting be proc create from Dict
    Let circular_deps be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 104

    Let target_names be proc keys from Dict with dependencies
    Let target_count be proc size from List with target_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than target_count:
        Let target_name be proc get from List with target_names, i
        Let is_visited be proc contains from Dict with visited, target_name

        If is_visited is equal to 0:
            proc detect_cycle_from_cmake_target with analyzer, target_name, visited, visiting, circular_deps
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
DFS visit: marks target as visiting, recurses into dependencies, then
marks visited and removes from visiting. A dependency found in the
visiting set indicates a back-edge (cycle). Three-colour algorithm
(unvisited/visiting/visited) handles diamond dependencies correctly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "detect_cycle_from_cmake_target" takes analyzer as Integer, target_name as Integer, visited as Integer, visiting as Integer, circular_deps as Integer:
    Note: Detect cycles starting from specific target

    proc set from Dict with visiting, target_name, 1

    Let dependencies be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 72
    Let target_deps be proc get from Dict with dependencies, target_name

    If target_deps is not equal to 0:
        Let dep_count be proc size from List with target_deps
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than dep_count:
            Let dep_name be proc get from List with target_deps, i
            Let is_visiting be proc contains from Dict with visiting, dep_name

            If is_visiting is equal to 1:
                Note: Cycle detected
                Let cycle_info be proc string_concat from StringCore with target_name, " -> "
                Set cycle_info to proc string_concat from StringCore with cycle_info, dep_name
                proc add from List with circular_deps, cycle_info

                Let error be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Circular dependency detected: ", cycle_info
                proc add_cmake_validation_error with analyzer, error
            Otherwise:
                Let is_visited be proc contains from Dict with visited, dep_name
                If is_visited is equal to 0:
                    proc detect_cycle_from_cmake_target with analyzer, dep_name, visited, visiting, circular_deps
                End If
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc remove from Dict with visiting, target_name
    proc set from Dict with visited, target_name, 1
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: UTILITY FUNCTIONS
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Linear scan against the canonical reserved-name list (ALL, CLEAN, INSTALL,
PACKAGE, RUN_TESTS, test, help). Building the list per call costs an
allocation but the function is called rarely (only during target-name
validation), so the readability benefit outweighs caching.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_cmake_reserved_name" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if name is reserved by CMake

    Note: Check common reserved target names
    Let reserved_names be proc create from List
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "ALL"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "CLEAN"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "INSTALL"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "PACKAGE"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "RUN_TESTS"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "test"
    proc add from List with reserved_names, "help"

    Let name_count be proc size from List with reserved_names
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than name_count:
        Let reserved_name be proc get from List with reserved_names, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, reserved_name
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
add_library(name) defaults to STATIC when no type is specified. With
add_library(name TYPE), the second arg is one of STATIC/SHARED/MODULE/
INTERFACE. If the second arg is something else (e.g., a source file),
we still default to STATIC since that's CMake's implicit behaviour.
@End Reasoning
Process called "determine_library_type" takes args as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Determine library type from add_library arguments

    Let arg_count be proc size from List with args
    If arg_count is less than 2:
        Return "STATIC"  Note: Default type
    End If

    Let type_arg be proc get from List with args, 1

    Let is_static be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_arg, "STATIC"
    If is_static is equal to 1:
        Return "STATIC"
    End If

    Let is_shared be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_arg, "SHARED"
    If is_shared is equal to 1:
        Return "SHARED"
    End If

    Let is_module be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_arg, "MODULE"
    If is_module is equal to 1:
        Return "MODULE"
    End If

    Let is_interface be proc string_equals from StringCore with type_arg, "INTERFACE"
    If is_interface is equal to 1:
        Return "INTERFACE"
    End If

    Note: Not a library type keyword, assume default
    Return "STATIC"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Compares against the canonical supported generator-expression names
(CONFIG, PLATFORM_ID, *_COMPILER_ID, TARGET_EXISTS, INSTALL/BUILD_INTERFACE,
etc.). Unknown names emit a warning rather than an error because new
CMake versions may legitimately add generators we don't know about.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_generator_name" takes analyzer as Integer, generator_name as Integer:
    Note: Validate generator expression name is supported

    Note: Check common generator expressions
    Let supported_generators be proc create from List
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "CONFIG"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "PLATFORM_ID"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "C_COMPILER_ID"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "CXX_COMPILER_ID"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "TARGET_EXISTS"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "TARGET_NAME_IF_EXISTS"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "COMPILE_LANG_AND_ID"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "INSTALL_INTERFACE"
    proc add from List with supported_generators, "BUILD_INTERFACE"

    Let generator_count be proc size from List with supported_generators
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than generator_count:
        Let supported_gen be proc get from List with supported_generators, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with generator_name, supported_gen
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let warning be proc string_concat from StringCore with "Unknown generator expression: ", generator_name
    proc add_cmake_validation_warning with analyzer, warning
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: ERROR HANDLING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records a fatal semantic error: stores the message at offset 152 and sets
the has_error flag at offset 160. Unlike add_cmake_validation_error which
accumulates, this is a sticky one-shot flag for unrecoverable failures.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_cmake_semantic_error" takes analyzer as Integer, error_message as Integer:
    Note: Set semantic analysis error

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 152, error_message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 160, 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validation errors are independent from the sticky has_error flag set by
set_cmake_semantic_error: a CMake project can have many recoverable validation
failures (undefined target referenced, mismatched argument count, etc.) that
should be collected so the user sees the full report, not just the first
issue. This append-only stream preserves source order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the validation_errors List from offset 136 and appends the borrowed
error_message StringCore pointer. Ownership policy: the analyzer's destructor
walks this list and frees each entry, so callers must pass a heap-owned
string (typically allocated immediately before the call).
@End Implementation

Process called "add_cmake_validation_error" takes analyzer as Integer, error_message as Integer:
    Note: Add validation error to error list

    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 136
    proc add from List with errors, error_message
End Process

@Reasoning:
Warnings vs errors are tracked in separate streams so the diagnostic reporter
can apply different severity formatting (color, exit code) without rescanning.
A warning never sets has_error, allowing builds to continue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Mirror of add_cmake_validation_error against the validation_warnings list at
offset 144. Same ownership policy: list destructor will free each warning
string, so callers pass heap-owned StringCore handles.
@End Implementation

Process called "add_cmake_validation_warning" takes analyzer as Integer, warning_message as Integer:
    Note: Add validation warning to warning list

    Let warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 144
    proc add from List with warnings, warning_message
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry point that bundles create_cmake_semantic_analyzer +
analyze_cmake_project for callers that want a one-shot analysis without
managing analyzer lifetime themselves (driver pipeline, language server).
The returned analyzer carries every diagnostic stream and graph result.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates a fresh analyzer; on OOM returns 0 (caller treats as fatal). Calls
analyze_cmake_project which walks the AST and populates targets, variables,
dependencies and diagnostic lists. The intermediate result is discarded
because the analyzer itself is the public artifact.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
cmake_ast originates from user CMakeLists.txt files; routine never reads
past the AST node graph so it is safe against malformed but well-formed
trees. Memory-exhaustion safety relies on create_cmake_semantic_analyzer's
allocation checks.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "cmake_semantic_analyze" takes cmake_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Perform semantic analysis on CMake AST

    Let analyzer be proc create_cmake_semantic_analyzer
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let result be proc analyze_cmake_project with analyzer, cmake_ast
    Return analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public accessor for the validation_errors List the diagnostic emitter walks
when formatting build report output. Returning 0 when analyzer is null lets
callers chain accessors without null-checking the analyzer each time.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads offset 136 (validation_errors List handle). Returns a BORROWED
pointer - the analyzer's destructor owns the list; consumers must not
free or destroy it.
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_get_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get validation errors from semantic analysis

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 136
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric public accessor for the validation_warnings List. Kept separate
from errors so warning-only builds (CMake's default for many issues) can be
reported without flagging the build as failed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads offset 144 (validation_warnings List handle); borrowed pointer
returned exactly as for the errors accessor.
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_get_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get validation warnings from semantic analysis

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 144
End Process

@Reasoning:
Cycle detection on the dependency graph runs once during analyze; this
accessor exposes the cached cycle list so build scripts and IDEs can flag
them without re-running Tarjan/Kosaraju. Each entry is a list of target
names forming one SCC.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads offset 104 (circular_dependencies List handle). Borrowed pointer;
ownership stays with the analyzer.
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_get_circular_dependencies" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get circular dependencies found during analysis

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 104
End Process

@Reasoning:
After dependency analysis the undefined_targets list contains every name
referenced by target_link_libraries/add_dependencies that was never created
via add_executable/add_library. Exposed so IDEs can underline the offending
references in CMakeLists.txt source.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads offset 112 (undefined_targets List handle). Borrowed pointer.
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_get_undefined_targets" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get undefined targets found during analysis

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 112
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each CMake policy CMP00xx has three states (OLD, NEW, unset) and trigger
warnings when called while unset on the active policy version. The analyzer
collects those warnings into a dedicated stream so callers can suppress
policy noise independently from real validation warnings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads offset 128 (policy_warnings List handle). Borrowed pointer.
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_get_policy_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get CMake policy warnings from analysis

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 128
End Process

@Reasoning:
Drivers need a single integer "did analysis succeed" check rather than a
list pointer. Returning the actual error count (not just 0/1) lets callers
pretty-print "N errors" without re-measuring the list. Null analyzer is
treated as having 1 error so failures upstream propagate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads validation_errors at offset 136 and returns List.size. When the
analyzer pointer is null returns 1 to indicate failure (the allocation
failed). Non-null analyzer with empty list returns 0 (success).
@End Implementation

Process called "cmake_semantic_has_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if semantic analysis found any errors

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 136
    Let error_count be proc size from List with errors
    Return error_count
End Process